        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 2:27AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 227 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
east of Scraper, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Gentry...                         Lake Francis...
Proctor...                        Westville...
Fairmount...                      Cincinnati...
Savoy...                          Decatur...
Ballard...                        Siloam Springs...
Springtown...                     Wedington...
Gallitin...                       Cherokee City...
Watts...                          West Siloam Springs...
Natural Falls State Park...       Twin Oaks...
Colcord...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for northwestern
Arkansas...and northeastern and east central Oklahoma.</instruction>
